name: morning
description:
Diesel Head: "Are you sure we're going the right way?"

Gratia: "Urgh! I'm holding the map, aren't I?"

Wargle, the Third of his name: "Wargle, wargle. Wargle"

Diesel Head: "Good point. We should ask for directions."

Gratia: "Uh-huh. I'm sure the alley-way denizens will be oh-so-
helpful, right before they rob us, and smoke poor Wargle here."

Wargle, the Third of his name: "Wargle wargle wargle!!"

Gratia: "Exactly. Just keep walking, and let me do the thinking."
